headline: Changing Restrictions on Russian Gas to Europe Would Disproportionately Impact US LNG Exports, New S&P Global Commodity Insights Study Finds
summary: The United States, which currently supplies half of Europe's liquefied natural gas (LNG) imports and roughly 15% of the continent's total gas supply, would be disproportionately impacted if current restrictions on Russian gas and LNG were to change, a new S&P Global Commodity Insights study finds.
